# Hono Backend Patterns

## Route Structure

- Use `app.route()` for modular route mounting in `src/index.ts`
- Each route file exports a `Hono` instance
- Validate request bodies with Zod schemas from `@personalclaw/shared`
- Return consistent JSON: `{ data }` for success, `{ error, message }` for failures

## Channel Adapter

- Agent engine depends on `ChannelAdapter` interface, never on platform SDKs
- Platform-specific code (Slack, Discord, etc.) lives in `src/<platform>/`
- Each platform constructs its adapter and passes it to `AgentEngine.run()`
- Extract `channelId`, `userId`, `threadId` from platform event context

## Thread Safety

- Always acquire thread lock (`withThreadLock`) before agent execution
- Thread lock is a mutex keyed by `threadId` to prevent concurrent processing

## Observability

- Use LogTape for all logging -- never use `console.*` (see `logging.mdc` rule)
- Log cost after every `generateText` / `streamText` call via `CostTracker`
- Include `externalUserId` in all logs, conversations, and usage records
- Emit lifecycle hooks at correct points via `HooksEngine`

## Agent Engine

- Use Vercel AI SDK `generateText()` with `maxSteps` for multi-step execution
- Build system prompt via `PromptComposer` (respects `promptInjectMode`)
- Merge MCP tools with native memory tools
- Run guardrails pre/post processing around agent loop
- Persist conversation after each successful run

## Config Hot-Reload

- Call `emitConfigChange()` after any config update in routes
- Agent engine listens for config changes and reloads without restart
